FBIS4-43495 "drweu117__a94021" FBIS-WEU-94-117-A Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 ANNEX Italy & Vatican City Martino Reassures EU Commissioner Martino Reassures EU Commissioner BR1706130094 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1650 GMT 16 Jun 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY BR1706130094 Rome ANSAMAIL Database English BFN [Unattributed article: "Martino Reassures Van Miert on Privatizations"] [Text] (ANSA) Rome, June 16 -- Italy's privatizations will take place with full respect for European Union [EU] competition rules, Foreign Minister Antonio Martino reassured the EU commissioner for Competition, Karel van Miert, at a meeting here Thursday [16 June]. A ministry communique said the meeting took place in a "cordial climate" and also covered a wide range of issues concerning European anti-trust and competition regulations, focussing on the new Rome government's "orientations" for privatizations. Budget Minister Giancarlo Pagliarini also met Van Miert and discussed state aid to industry, privatizations, regional aid and tax rules for payments made by employers for pensions and welfare, a communique said. Van Miert urged Rome to prepare as soon as possible a list of areas that may be eligible for EU funds. Most of the EU funds set aside for development and infrastructure projects in southern Italy over the past several years have not been used.
